---
import { ArrowUpRight } from "@lucide/astro";
import BaseLayout from "../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { links } from "../../../data/site.js";
import { claimsById } from "../../../data/claims.js";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Berkeley and MoBagel AI product strategy | Kevin Astuhuaman"
  description="Kevin Astuhuaman's Berkeley Haas Open Innovation Squad work on AI product adoption, high-fidelity prototyping, roadmap, business model, and go-to-market recommendations for MoBagel."
  path="/projects/berkeley-mobagel-ai-gtm/"
  pageType="article"
  about="AI product strategy and go-to-market for the Fujitsu and MoBagel challenge"
>
  <header class="page-hero mobagel-hero">
    <div class="section-shell">
      <p class="eyebrow">Berkeley Haas Open Innovation Squad | December 2024-May 2025</p>
      <h1>Making an AI platform easier to understand, adopt, and take to market.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        I worked on the Fujitsu and MoBagel challenge across product discovery, feature and UX concepts, a high-fidelity Figma prototype, roadmap, business model, and United States go-to-market recommendations.
      </p>
      <div class="case-meta">
        <span><strong>Role:</strong> AI Product Manager</span>
        <span><strong>Context:</strong> Berkeley Open Innovation challenge</span>
        <span><strong>Focus:</strong> Product adoption and GTM</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <article class="article-shell">
    <p class="eyebrow">The product tension</p>
    <h2>Powerful AI is not useful if a business user cannot see the path from question to decision.</h2>
    <p>
      MoBagel was presented in the challenge as an AI and machine-learning platform designed to simplify how businesses adopt AI. The product question was broader than feature discovery: how should the experience, value proposition, pricing, partnerships, and roadmap work together for a United States customer?
    </p>

    <figure class="prototype-reconstruction" aria-labelledby="prototype-caption">
      <div class="prototype-chrome">
        <div class="prototype-topbar"><span>AI adoption workspace</span><small>Public-safe reconstruction</small></div>
        <div class="prototype-body">
          <nav aria-label="Reconstructed product steps" tabindex="0">
            <span class="active">01 Frame</span>
            <span>02 Connect</span>
            <span>03 Explore</span>
            <span>04 Activate</span>
          </nav>
          <section>
            <p class="prototype-kicker">Business question</p>
            <h3>Which customer segment is most likely to adopt this offer?</h3>
            <div class="prototype-input"><span>Goal</span><strong>Prioritize a segment for the U.S. launch</strong></div>
            <div class="prototype-grid">
              <div><span>Audience</span><strong>Business operator</strong></div>
              <div><span>Decision</span><strong>Market entry</strong></div>
              <div><span>Success signal</span><strong>Repeated weekly use</strong></div>
            </div>
          </section>
          <aside>
            <span>Guided next step</span>
            <h4>Connect the smallest useful data set.</h4>
            <p>Explain what is required, what remains optional, and how the result will change the decision.</p>
            <button type="button" disabled>Review data requirements</button>
          </aside>
        </div>
      </div>
      <figcaption id="prototype-caption"><strong>Reconstructed experience direction</strong><span>The approved Figma deliverable is private; this original, synthetic interface makes the public product logic inspectable without presenting it as client work.</span></figcaption>
    </figure>

    <div class="adoption-map" aria-label="Public-safe AI product adoption framework">
      <div><span>01</span><strong>Business question</strong><p>Start with the decision a non-technical user needs to make.</p></div>
      <div><span>02</span><strong>Guided workflow</strong><p>Turn data and modeling complexity into understandable product steps.</p></div>
      <div><span>03</span><strong>Visible result</strong><p>Connect the output to an action, not merely a generated insight.</p></div>
      <div><span>04</span><strong>Adoption loop</strong><p>Align packaging, usage, partnerships, and roadmap with repeated value.</p></div>
    </div>

    <h2>The work connected product design with market entry.</h2>
    <div class="workstreams">
      <section>
        <p class="eyebrow">Discover</p>
        <h3>Research the user and category</h3>
        <p>Product and competitive research focused the opportunity around non-technical users who needed analysis and automation without becoming machine-learning specialists.</p>
      </section>
      <section>
        <p class="eyebrow">Prototype</p>
        <h3>Make the product direction tangible</h3>
        <p>Feature and UX concepts were carried into a high-fidelity Figma prototype so the team could evaluate a product experience, not only a written recommendation.</p>
      </section>
      <section>
        <p class="eyebrow">Sequence</p>
        <h3>Connect the prototype to a roadmap</h3>
        <p>The roadmap linked user needs, product capabilities, and differentiated value rather than treating the prototype as an isolated design exercise.</p>
      </section>
      <section>
        <p class="eyebrow">Go to market</p>
        <h3>Design how adoption would happen</h3>
        <p>Recommendations covered positioning, partnership channels, a business model, and usage-based pricing for United States expansion.</p>
      </section>
    </div>

    <h2>Three decisions carried the strategy.</h2>
    <dl class="decision-list">
      <div class="decision">
        <dt>Lead with the user's decision, not the model</dt>
        <dd>The product story needed to explain what a business user could accomplish before explaining the AI and machine-learning machinery underneath.</dd>
      </div>
      <div class="decision">
        <dt>Use a high-fidelity prototype to test the proposition</dt>
        <dd>A polished prototype made workflow, hierarchy, and usability assumptions inspectable before roadmap or market commitments.</dd>
      </div>
      <div class="decision">
        <dt>Treat GTM as part of the product</dt>
        <dd>Pricing, partnerships, packaging, and onboarding determine whether an AI capability becomes a repeated workflow or an interesting demo.</dd>
      </div>
    </dl>

    <aside class="source-note">
      <strong>Evidence boundary</strong>
      <p>Kevin's role and deliverables are public resume claims. {claimsById["berkeley-mobagel-brief"].statement} No funding, customer, or production claims are inferred from the official program listing.</p>
    </aside>

    <div class="button-row final-actions">
      <a class="button button-dark" href={links.berkeleyMobagel}>Open Berkeley's challenge brief <ArrowUpRight aria-hidden="true" size={17} /></a>
      <a class="button" href="/resume/">View resume</a>
      <a class="button" href="/contact/">Contact Kevin</a>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .mobagel-hero {
    background: #243238;
  }

  .prototype-reconstruction {
    margin: 48px 0 68px;
    overflow: hidden;
    border: 1px solid #203735;
    border-radius: 7px;
    background: #e9f0ee;
  }

  .prototype-chrome {
    margin: clamp(18px, 4vw, 42px);
    overflow: hidden;
    border: 1px solid #203735;
    border-radius: 4px;
    background: #f9fbfa;
    box-shadow: 16px 18px 0 rgba(15,78,70,.09);
  }

  .prototype-topbar {
    display: flex;
    min-height: 58px;
    padding: 14px 18px;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 20px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #203735;
    font-weight: 780;
  }

  .prototype-topbar small { color: #5b6866; font-weight: 650; }

  .prototype-body {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 150px minmax(0, 1fr) 260px;
    min-height: 430px;
  }

  .prototype-body nav {
    display: flex;
    padding: 24px 14px;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 7px;
    border-right: 1px solid #c8d4d2;
    background: #163d38;
  }

  .prototype-body nav span {
    padding: 11px 10px;
    color: #c6d4d1;
    font-size: .74rem;
    font-weight: 720;
  }

  .prototype-body nav .active { background: #d8ff52; color: #10221f; }

  .prototype-body > section { padding: 42px 34px; }
  .prototype-kicker { margin: 0; color: #08766a; font-size: .7rem; font-weight: 820; letter-spacing: .1em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .prototype-body h3 { max-width: 570px; margin: 15px 0 34px; font-size: clamp(1.65rem, 3.4vw, 2.7rem); letter-spacing: -.04em; }

  .prototype-input,
  .prototype-grid > div {
    display: grid;
    gap: 8px;
    padding: 16px;
    border: 1px solid #c8d4d2;
    background: white;
  }

  .prototype-input span,
  .prototype-grid span,
  .prototype-body aside > span { color: #5b6866; font-size: .67rem; font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: .08em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .prototype-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); margin-top: 12px; }
  .prototype-grid > div + div { border-left: 0; }
  .prototype-grid strong { font-size: .8rem; }

  .prototype-body aside {
    padding: 34px 26px;
    border-left: 1px solid #c8d4d2;
    background: #eff5f3;
  }

  .prototype-body aside h4 { margin: 52px 0 14px; font-size: 1.35rem; }
  .prototype-body aside p { color: #515e5c; font-size: .86rem; }
  .prototype-body aside button { width: 100%; margin-top: 26px; padding: 13px; border: 1px solid #163d38; background: #163d38; color: white; font-weight: 760; }

  .prototype-reconstruction figcaption {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 240px 1fr;
    gap: 22px;
    padding: 18px 22px;
    border-top: 1px solid #203735;
    background: white;
    font-size: .8rem;
  }

  .prototype-reconstruction figcaption span { color: #5b6866; }

  .adoption-map {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    margin: 48px 0 62px;
    border-top: 1px solid #c8d4d2;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #c8d4d2;
  }

  .adoption-map > div {
    min-height: 220px;
    padding: 24px 22px 22px 0;
  }

  .adoption-map > div + div {
    padding-left: 22px;
    border-left: 1px solid #c8d4d2;
  }

  .adoption-map span,
  .adoption-map strong {
    display: block;
  }

  .adoption-map span {
    color: #06645b;
    font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
  }

  .adoption-map strong {
    margin-top: 46px;
  }

  .adoption-map p {
    color: #515e5c;
    font-size: 0.84rem;
  }

  .workstreams {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    margin: 42px 0 64px;
    border: 1px solid #c8d4d2;
  }

  .workstreams section {
    min-height: 270px;
    padding: 28px;
  }

  .workstreams section:nth-child(2n) {
    border-left: 1px solid #c8d4d2;
  }

  .workstreams section:nth-child(n + 3) {
    border-top: 1px solid #c8d4d2;
  }

  .workstreams h3 {
    margin-top: 28px;
    font-size: 1.55rem;
  }

  .workstreams p:last-child {
    color: #515e5c;
  }

  .source-note {
    margin: 48px 0;
    padding: 22px 24px;
    border-left: 4px solid #08766a;
    background: #edf6f4;
  }

  .source-note p {
    margin: 8px 0 0;
    color: #515e5c;
  }

  .final-actions {
    margin-top: 56px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 700px) {
    .prototype-body {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .prototype-body nav {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
      padding: 10px;
      border-right: 0;
      border-bottom: 1px solid #c8d4d2;
    }

    .prototype-body nav span {
      min-width: 0;
      padding: 10px 8px;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .prototype-body > section { padding: 28px 22px; }
    .prototype-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .prototype-grid > div + div { border-top: 0; border-left: 1px solid #c8d4d2; }
    .prototype-body aside { border-top: 1px solid #c8d4d2; border-left: 0; }
    .prototype-reconstruction figcaption { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }

    .adoption-map,
    .workstreams {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .adoption-map > div {
      min-height: 0;
      padding: 20px 0;
    }

    .adoption-map > div + div,
    .workstreams section:nth-child(2n) {
      padding-left: 0;
      border-left: 0;
      border-top: 1px solid #c8d4d2;
    }

    .adoption-map strong {
      margin-top: 12px;
    }

    .workstreams section,
    .workstreams section:nth-child(n + 3) {
      min-height: 0;
      padding: 22px;
      border-top: 1px solid #c8d4d2;
    }

    .workstreams section:first-child {
      border-top: 0;
    }
  }
</style>
